
- make sure that the KOBJ_ROOT environment var is set in the .bashrc
  file

- set the WEB_ROOT environment variable

- copy httpd-perl.conf.example to ~/conf/extra/httpd-perl.conf and
  ensure it's being loaded in ~/conf/httpd.conf (You can use 
  bin/install-httpd-conf to copy the file.)

- You need to install

  Apache
  mod_perl
  Geo::IP (www.maxmind.com)
  LWP::Simple - CPAN
  DateTime - CPAN
  XML::XPath - CPAN
  SVN::Client - use  sudo yum install subversion-perl
  HOP::Parser - CPAN
  HOP::Lexer - CPAN
  Log::Log4perl - CPAN
  HTML::Template - CPAN
  File::Find::Rule - CPAN
  Test::LongString - CPAN

  Running $KOBJ_ROOT/t/smoke dev/use.t will ensure you've got all the
  right libraries

- Set up an SVN user for the rules repository
  -- make sure it starts automatically (use chkconfig)
